This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel technique for regularizing deep neural networks through data augmentation. It also involves meta-learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper also uses image datasets such as CIFAR-10 and SVHN, which are commonly used in computer vision research (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper involves semi-supervised learning (SSL), which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) experiments, which could place it under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
